        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 9:58PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 958 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 37
miles north of Forsyth, or 36 miles northwest of Miles City, moving
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Miles City, Angela, Rock Springs, Hathaway, Matthews Recreation
Area and Strawberry Hill Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
